resources.description:
 > #### This methods return all contacts registered in Data base.

 > **GET** _/v1/contacts

- **Request**
  > - Body: *no body*

- **Response**



>     
    "httpStatusCode": int,
    "success": boolean,
    "message": string,
    "data": [
      {
        "id": int
        "name":{
         "firstName":string,
          "lastName":string
        },
        "email":string,
        "phoneNumbers":[
          {
            "number":string
          }
        ]
      }
    ]

 > #### This method returns a contact given an identifier.

 > **GET** _/v1/contacts/***id:int***

- **Request**
  > - Body: *no body*

- **Response**



>     
    "httpStatusCode": int,
    "success": boolean,
    "message": string,
    "data": {
        "id": int
        "name":{
         "firstName":string,
         "lastName":string
        },
        "email":string,
        "phoneNumbers":[
          {
            "number":string
          }
        ]
     }

 > #### This method creates a contact and saves it in the database.

 > **POST** _/v1/contacts/

- **Request**
  > - type: ***application/json***
  > - Body:
          {
            required "FirstName":string, 
	        required "LastName":string,
	        required "EmailAddress":string,
	                 "PhoneNumbers":[string]
         }

- **Response**



>     
    "httpStatusCode": int,
    "success": boolean,
    "message": string,
    "data": {
        "id": int
        "name":{
         "firstName":string,
         "lastName":string
        },
        "email":string,
        "phoneNumbers":[
          {
            "number":string
          }
        ]
     }

> #### This method updates a contact registered in the database.

 > **PUT** _/v1/contacts/***id:int***

- **Request**
  > - Note: **You can update one or more attributes, sending only the desired ones in the request body.**
  > - type: ***application/json***
  > - Body:
          {
            "FirstName":string, 
	        "LastName":string,
	        "EmailAddress":string,
	        "PhoneNumbers":[string]
         }

- **Response**



>     
    "httpStatusCode": int,
    "success": boolean,
    "message": string,
    "data": {
        "id": int
        "name":{
         "firstName":string,
         "lastName":string
        },
        "email":string,
        "phoneNumbers":[
          {
            "number":string
          }
        ]
     }

> #### This method deletes a contact registered in the database.

 > **DELETE** _/v1/contacts/***id:int***

- **Request**
  > - Body: no body

- **Response**



>     
    "httpStatusCode": int,
    "success": boolean,
    "message": string,
    "data": {
        "id": int
        "name":{
         "firstName":string,
         "lastName":string
        },
        "email":string,
        "phoneNumbers":[
          {
            "number":string
          }
        ]
     }
